    "Conversely, when the output probabilities are biased on average but the model's class-wise performance is balanced, this hidden bias could result in actual performance disparities on more difficult instances.",
    "We therefore suggest reporting both measures.",
    "3 Experimental Setting",
    "We evaluate models on 279 diverse tasks from the SUPER-NATURALINSTRUCTIONS benchmark (Wang et al., 2022).",
    "We select all available classification and multi-choice question answering tasks where the output space is a set of predefined labels, such as \"yes/no\" or \"A/B/C\"."
